    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Goldbeaters in Nahua culture who hammered gold into sheets and then modified it with embossing, engracing, cutting, and perforating. Literally, "those who beat gold."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
